news.title: Bengaluru Metro will have 170km network, 17 lakh ridership by 2024: BMRCL MD
news.para: Parwez said: “Challaghatta station (2km Kengeri-Challaghatta extension) will be ready by September 2022 and the 3km stretch of Nagasandra-Bangalore International Exhibition Centre (Madavara) will be operational by October-November 2022”.

news.title: Chennai metro floats tender again for tough 5.8 km undergound stretch
news.para: The first tender floated for the stretch in January 2021 was one among six construction tenders cancelled as they either did not find many takers or quoted more than the actual estimate. The 118.9km phase-2 is expected to be ready by 2025.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body to fast-track release of development rights certificates
news.para: The DRCs will be issued to those who had surrendered their land for road widening five years prior to the enactment of the Karnataka Town and Country Planning (Amendment) Act, 2021, that came into effect on October 7, 2021.

news.title: Mumbai: Property tax waiver to cost BMC Rs 463 crore, says Iqbal Chahal
news.para: Chahal said till December 31, the BMC had also collected Rs 3,450 crore in property tax when its target was only Rs 800 crore.

news.title: Allottees want YEIDA to roll back additional land premium
news.para: In December last year, the Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) had asked industrial plot allottees, who applied for its one-time settlement scheme, to pay a “no litigation incentive” along with the adjusted premium.

news.title: KIADB to allot land to industries on 10-year lease-cum-sale basis
news.para: "The amendment will encourage the industry for further expansion and investment as allotted land will be under their ownership once they successfully run the company," he said.

news.title: Hassan development body to construct layout in 1,060 acres on outskirts
news.para: The earmarked area is located in and around surrounding villages of Buvanahalli where the airport project is being executed. About 1,700 farmers are parting with their farm land to Huda’s new layout project.

news.title: Emaar scam accused moves HC, seeks halt to ED framing charges
news.para: Though the CBI made Ranga Rao an accused in the Emaar case and also arrayed his firm, Stylish Homes, as the accused entity, he had turned an approver for the CBI.

news.title: Kerala: Digital land survey in Ernakulam to begin next week
news.para: The resurvey office at Thrikkakara has informed that the process of installing GPS points in Poonithura village has already begun.

news.title: Indore civic body to make rainwater harvesting compulsory
news.para: “We have proposed amendments to the IMC’s building permission bylaws and invited claims and objections to make roof top rain harvesting system mandatory in all buildings constructed in municipal limits of Indore. We hope to make it compulsory within a month or so,” IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal

news.title: China makes REITs push to speed up infrastructure investment
news.para: NDRC urged its local bureaus to step up publicity, cut red tape, and improve services, so that more infrastructure projects can be listed in the form of REITs, according to a notice posted on the agency's website on Friday.

news.title: Gurgaon court orders police to register FIR against MGF by Sunday
news.para: "The SHO City, Gurugram is also directed to appear in person in court on January 2 at about 11 am and submit his written reply for not registering the FIR despite the court order,” the court has said on Saturday. As per the court order, the SHO did not register the FIR for two days after the first order.

news.title: China Evergrande Group revises payment plan for wealth unit investors
news.para: Evergrande, whose $19 billion in international bonds are deemed to be in cross-default by rating agencies after the developer missed a deadline to pay coupons earlier this month, did not pay offshore coupons due earlier this week.

news.title: Mumbai: No property tax on residential properties up to 500 sq ft
news.para: ​​The waiver comes ahead of Mumbai municipal corporation elections due next month. The CM has asked the administration to implement the decision with immediate effect, the release said.

news.title: Kerala government launches campaign to provide housing for landless poor
news.para: Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan on Friday said this campaign aims at providing land and housing to 2.5 lakh families within three years with the generous support and donations from the public.
